<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-22T12:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-22T12:36:00-05:00" n="966" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d966">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13858.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to
                                Mexico to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-22T11:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 22, 1914, 11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>218. General Blanco today assumed full command of the situation in the
                            Federal District, appointing provisionally governor, police inspector
                            and minor officials. I was reliably informed that this took place after
                            serious disagreement between him and Obregón who as his senior officer
                            commanded him to abandon the city, which he strongly refused to do.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>